<subSubSection pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
The species in this genus are mainly associated with plants in the family 
<taxonomicName genus="Euphorbiaceae" lsidName="Euphorbiaceae" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" rank="genus">Euphorbiaceae</taxonomicName>
, but also with Leguminosae and 
<taxonomicName genus="Malvaceae" lsidName="Malvaceae" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" rank="genus">Malvaceae</taxonomicName>
(cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Jolivet, P" journalOrPublisher="An essay about the relationships between the leaf-beetles and their food-plants. Backhuys Publishers, Leiden" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" title="Host-plants of Chrysomelidae of the World." year="1995">Jolivet and Hawkeswood 1995</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pollard, DG" journalOrPublisher="Diderot &amp; D'Alembert, premiers editeurs de l'Encyclopedie. Histoire Naturelle. Insectes. Tome IV. Chez Panckoucke, Paris" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" title="Halticinae of the Sudan. Bull. Entomol. Res. 47: 73 − 87." url="10.1017/S0007485300046538" year="1957">Pollard 1957</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
